content: Singaporean football clubFootball club **Cairnhill Football Club** is a former Singapore football club which competed in the [Singapore National Football League](/wiki/Singapore_National_Football_League) in the 1980s. The club won the Division 3 title in 1975 and the Division 2 title in 1982. In 1981, Cairnhill reached the quarterfinals of the President's Cup.
